OL,5, One of Africa's most-celebrated authors
OL,6, and playwrights, Ghanaian Ama Ata      
OL,7, Aidoo, has died aged 81.               
OL,9,FA renowned feminist, she depicted and  
OL,10,Fcelebrated the condition of African    
OL,11,Fwomen in works such as The Dilemma of a
OL,12,FGhost, Our Sister Killjoy and Changes. 
OL,14,FShe opposed what she described as a    
OL,15,F"Western perception that the African   
OL,16,Ffemale is a downtrodden wretch".       
OL,18,FShe also served as education minister  
OL,19,Fin the early 1980s but resigned when   
OL,20,Fshe could not make education free.     
